Xavier Suspends Four Players Following Basketball Brawl Against Cincinnati

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-12-11T21:24:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/xavier-suspends-four-players-following-basketball-brawl-against-cincinnati.html
Xavier University  suspended four
basketball players for their involvement in a brawl during
yesterday’s 76-53 win over the University of Cincinnati.  Xavier said on its website that Dezmine Wells and Landen
Amos will each sit out four games, Mark Lyons will serve a two-
game ban and Tu Holloway received a one-game suspension.  Cincinnati also suspended four players earlier today, with
six-game bans given to Yancy Gates, Octavius Ellis and Cheikh
Mbodj. Ge’Lawn Guyn will sit out one game, the Bearcats said in
a statement on their website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  